Some of the undeclared gold jewelry nabbed at the JKIA.   KRA officers in conjunction with a multi-agency team have impounded 4.8kg of gold that was being smuggled through JKIA.  According to a statement from the Kenya Revenue Authority, 30 women were arrested on Tuesday night with the undeclared gold jewelry at the Jomo Kenyatta International Airport.  KRA said its officers stationed at JKIA identified the women who were departing from Nairobi.  They were aboard Qatar Airways flight 1342 on transit to Doha, arriving in Mumbai, India, onboard QR flight 558 at 20:50 hours.  War that pushed Boers to trek from S Africa to Eldoret  Miguna Miguna lands on Tuesday  Small-scale miners predict bright future from gold refinery project  Why Gor Mahia and Tusker face huge task on venues for CAF ties Customs officers searched the passengers and discovered approximately 4.8kg of undeclared gold and jewelry. The market value of the items is said to be around Sh31 million.  All passengers are encouraged to declare all cargo at the ports of entry and exit as required by law.  The travelers are linked to three other female travellers who were arrested with 1kg of smuggled gold upon entering Mumbai on August 19, 2021,” read the statement.  According to the statement, all the women who were on board the flight were then asked to alight from the flight to allow investigations.  The jewelry, the authority said, has been deposited in a customs warehouse.    Re-opening of JKIA: Plans in top gear to resume post-COVID-19 after aviation sector takes huge hit  Suspended KQ employee Ali Gire resumes duty at JKIA, says his safety is not guaranteed  Developing Story: Body of the late MCA Cyrus Omondi has arrived in the country from Mumbai By Pkemoi Ngenoh | 15 hours ago By Kamore Maina and Winfrey Owino | 1 day ago By  Nzau Musau | 2 days ago By Pkemoi Ng'enoh | 5 days ago How robbers in four-hour siege at bank evaded police